Again he devoted himself mainly to quiet work. The years B.C. 46, 45, 44 constitute the period of his greatest literary pro- ductiveness.

After the crash of Caesar’s death, he displayed once more his old-time activity, opposing Antony, and writing letters in all directions to commanders and provincial governors, urging them to the loyal support of the republic.

31 l ante Victoriam : over Antony, who was besieging Deci- mus Brutus in Mutina. After the murder of Caesar the leading conspirators lingered for a time in Rome and then separated in various directions, some to take charge of provinces which had been assigned to them by Caesar. Among the latter was Deci- mus Brutus, whom Caesar had appointed to the government of Cisalpine Gaul. By a later arrangement Antony had got this province assigned to himself.
